// runtime/stdlib/vec_deque.kara
//
// `VecDeque[T]` — double-ended queue. Method surface
// (`new`, `push_front`, `push_back`, `pop_front`, `pop_back`,
// `len`, `is_empty`, `iter`) dispatches through the interpreter's
// hardcoded `eval_call` / `eval_method_call` paths today (codegen
// is a peer follow-up). Mirrors the `vec.kara` shape: opaque
// in-memory representation, no public fields, no `#[derive(...)]`.

struct VecDeque[=T] { }
